-- Maybank's Indonesian unit to sell $152.7 mln in bonds, sukuk
-- By Al-Zaquan Amer Hamzah
-- Fri Jun 20, 2014 03:20AM EDT
-- None



KUALA LUMPUR, June 20 (Reuters) - PT Bank Internasional Indonesia [BNIII.UL] (BII), a unit of Malaysia's Maybank <MBBM.KL>, said on Friday that it will sell 1.8 trillion rupiah ($152.67 million) of bonds and sukuk on June 19 to fund domestic loans.

BII will sell 300 billion rupiah of three-year sukuk mudharaba and 1.5 trillion rupiah of seven-year bonds as part of a plan to raise 4 trillion rupiah in the next few years, it told the local stock exchange.  PT HSBC Securities Indonesia, PT Indopremier Securities, PT Mandiri Sekuritas and PT Maybank Kim Eng Securities are the advisors for the deal.